      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAWBOURNE OZZY (5) is worth forgiving last start after finishing seventh (30.44) at Wentworth Park over 520m. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from four starts. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Can make amends. BIG TED (1) had been in super honest form hitting the frame three times on end before finishing fourth (25.92) at this track last time. Goes well out of this box with a win and five minor placings. Can figure in the finish. PURE BLUE (2) boasts a strong record this journey here with four wins and three minors from 10 tries. Placed last time (30.23) at Nowra in a Grade 4/5, finishing third and beaten half a length. Looks one of the chances. KING ZEAL (7) was strongly fancied last time on the back of a win two back but could only manage fifth (25.25) at this track.",
